[SN]TITLE[SN]
Family escape from Peebles house blaze

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A family - including a baby - have escaped injury after fire broke out in the early hours of the morning in their Scottish Borders home.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Emergency services were called to the blaze in the Bridgegate in Peebles at about 02:50.
Firefighters using breathing apparatus were able to extinguish the fire.
The baby was checked over by ambulance staff for suspected smoke inhalation but did not require hospital treatment.
